# Nova Project Structure

```
nova/
├── app/                    # Next.js app directory
├── components/            # Shared React components
├── lib/                   # Utility functions and shared logic
├── models/               # Data models and types
├── features/             # Feature-specific components and logic
├── locales/              # Internationalization files
├── public/               # Static assets
├── docs/                 # Documentation
│   ├── CHANGELOG.md      # Project changelog
│   └── PROJECT_SCOPE.md  # Project scope and requirements
├── .env.example          # Environment variables template
├── .gitignore           # Git ignore rules
├── next.config.js       # Next.js configuration
├── package.json         # Project dependencies and scripts
├── postcss.config.js    # PostCSS configuration
├── README.md            # Project overview and setup instructions
├── tailwind.config.js   # Tailwind CSS configuration
└── tsconfig.json        # TypeScript configuration
```

## Key Directories

- `app/`: Contains the Next.js application routes and pages
- `components/`: Reusable React components
- `lib/`: Shared utilities, hooks, and helper functions
- `models/`: TypeScript interfaces, types, and data models
- `features/`: Feature-specific components and business logic
- `locales/`: Internationalization files for multiple languages
- `public/`: Static assets like images, fonts, and icons
- `docs/`: Project documentation and specifications

## Development Setup

1. Clone the repository
2. Copy `.env.example` to `.env` and configure environment variables
3. Install dependencies: `npm install` or `yarn install`
4. Start development server: `npm run dev` or `yarn dev`

## Documentation

- `CHANGELOG.md`: Tracks all notable changes to the project
- `PROJECT_SCOPE.md`: Defines project requirements and architecture
- `README.md`: Project overview and setup instructions 